   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "I use `testmempoolaccept` for sanity-checking transactions I produce are valid in some app.\r\nI use a chain of unconfirmed transactions and cannot test the transaction relying on the precedent unconfirmed one, even though passed in the same array of transactions to `testmempoolaccept`.\r\n\r\nWanted to propose a PR, but reading the original `testmempoolaccept` PR it seems to have some precedent, so asking here before about the conceptual validity : what do you think of making `testmempoolaccept` test each transaction passed in the array as if all *valid* precedent transactions of the array were into the mempool ?",
